'''Jaintia Rajbari''' is located in [[Jaintiapur Upazila|Jaintiapur]], [[Sylhet]], [[Bangladesh]]. It was the residence of Kings of [[Jaintia Kingdom]]. The word "Jaintia" derived from the shrine of Jayanti Devi or Jainteswari, an incarnation of goddess Durga.<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://www.assamtribune.com/scripts/detailsnew.asp?id=jul0410/oth05|title = The Assam Tribune Online|website = www.assamtribune.com|access-date = 2016-05-07}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url = http://www.travel-bangladesh.net/jaintiapur-lost-kingdom|title = Jaintiapur: the lost kingdom - Travel-Bangladesh.Net|date = 2010-07-03|website = Travel-Bangladesh.Net|language = en-US|access-date = 2016-05-07}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url = https://books.google.com/books?id=T4ZVBAAAQBAJ|title = Engineering Geology for Society and Territory - Volume 8: Preservation of Cultural Heritage|last = Lollino|first = Giorgio|last2 = Giordan|first2 = Daniele|last3 = Marunteanu|first3 = Cristian|last4 = Christaras|first4 = Basiles|last5 = Yoshinori|first5 = Iwasaki|last6 = Margottini|first6 = Claudio|date = 2014-08-21|publisher = Springer|isbn = 9783319094083|page = 221|language = en}}</ref>

